🧩 1. Overview
Project Name: Secure Time‑Tracking System
This project is a lightweight, secure, and offline‑friendly time‑tracking application designed for small and medium‑sized companies.
It allows employees to clock in and out using personal accounts, while all activity logs are stored in an encrypted file accessible only through an authorized decryptor.

The goal of the project is to support digital transformation by replacing manual time‑tracking processes with a secure, auditable, and user‑friendly solution.

🏗️ 2. Architecture
Main Components
User Management Module  
Handles employee accounts, authentication, and admin‑level access.

Time‑Tracking Engine  
Automatically records check‑in and check‑out timestamps.

Encryption Layer  
Protects all stored data using a symmetric encryption algorithm (AES or similar).

Decryption Tool  
Allows authorized personnel to decrypt and review employee logs.

Storage System  
Encrypted file containing structured time‑tracking records.

Data Flow
User logs in with username + password

System validates credentials

User clocks in/out

Timestamp is appended to encrypted log file

Admin can decrypt logs using the decryptor tool

